article_title: Lowering Unemployment Rate Is a Tough Job
article_text:
There are two big questions about the unemployment rate. One is how low it should go. The other is how long it will take to get there.

Economists estimate that Thursday’s jobs report will show U.S. payrolls grew by 233,000 in June, pushing the unemployment rate to 5.4% from 5.5% in May. And with the job market looking strong, unemployment seems poised to go lower still.
